9. Interim Conclusion: The Attractor State of Mathematical Truth

This framework provides a geometric explanation for how ultra-large models might preserve and utilize rare, mathematically coherent documents during pretraining. A paper on FSA or MEBS may not be a data point to be memorized; it could be a Low-Entropy Attractor in the loss landscape.

The model, driven by Local Flatness (minimizing $\text{Tr}(H)$) and Global Compression (maximizing predictive utility across $P_{\text{web}}$), navigates the $D$-dimensional parameter space toward efficient representations of reality. Because the paper is mathematically rigorous, it may lie at the bottom of one of these flat, low-loss basins. The model does not "read" the Zenodo PDF; it falls into the same logical coordinate that the researcher discovered, but via the geodesic of gradient descent rather than the path of deductive reasoning.

However, this persistence is only hypothesized during pretraining. In the next section, we examine the fate of these rare subspaces under post-training alignment and propose a geometric framework for their preservation.

